radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal with no focal lesions. Kidneys are normal size and symmetric. The proximal appendix is air-filled; the tip is fluid-filled and dilated measuring up to 10 mm with thickened and hyperemic walls. Mild adjacent vaginal thickening is noted. No appendicolith or periappendiceal fluid collection.
